Birth statistics

2022-06-11

Albert B. Cook

Lets look at how Albert relates to the population of children in Germany1 as implemented in the childsds R package2.

Height

Alberts height of 108 cm at age 4.0 years corresponds to the 81.5% quantile among boys in Germany of that age.

Weight

Alberts weight of 19,100 g at age 4.0 years corresponds to the 82.6% quantile among boys in Germany of that age.

BMI

Alberts bmi of 16.38 kg/m at age 4.0 years corresponds to the 73.3% quantile among boys in Germany of that age.

  2. Vogel M (2022). childsds: Data and Methods Around Reference Values in Pediatrics. R package version 0.8.0, https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=childsds.
